---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
const pageTitle = "Our Philosophy — Student-Centered, Exam-Ready";
const pageDescription = "Grifi’s philosophy for students, teachers, and institutes: learning, mastery, discipline, health, and exam temperament.";
---

<Layout {title}={pageTitle} {description}={pageDescription}>
  <section class="container mx-auto px-4 py-16 md:py-24">
    <p class="mx-auto mb-3 w-fit rounded-full bg-primary/10 px-3 py-1 text-xs font-medium text-primary">Philosophy</p>
    <h1 class="max-w-3xl text-4xl font-bold leading-tight tracking-tight md:text-5xl">
      Student-centered learning for competitive excellence
    </h1>
    <p class="mt-4 max-w-3xl text-muted-foreground">
      Grifi is a startup building AI tools for students, teachers, and institutes—with a special focus on
      competitive exams. We are reimagining how we learn by placing the student at the center of every
      learning environment. Teachers act as mentors and gurus who guide, challenge, and support. Institutes
      provide structure, accountability, and community.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section id="ecosystem" class="container mx-auto px-4 py-10 md:py-14">
    <div class="grid gap-6 md:grid-cols-3">
      <div class="rounded-2xl border bg-card p-6 shadow-sm">
        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold">Student at the Center</h3>
        <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-muted-foreground">
          Every decision optimizes for the learner’s clarity, momentum, and confidence. Progress
          should feel visible, personalized, and motivating.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="rounded-2xl border bg-card p-6 shadow-sm">
        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold">Teacher as Mentor & Guru</h3>
        <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-muted-foreground">
          The teacher guides the journey—setting direction, calibrating difficulty, and cultivating
          discipline and curiosity.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="rounded-2xl border bg-card p-6 shadow-sm">
        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold">Institute as Scaffolding</h3>
        <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-muted-foreground">
          Institutes create the rhythm: timetables, milestones, feedback loops, and peer energy—so
          serious preparation becomes sustainable.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section id="journey" class="container mx-auto px-4 py-16 md:py-20">
    <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight">The learning journey</h2>
    <p class="mt-3 max-w-2xl text-muted-foreground">
      Preparation is a journey with distinct, reinforcing parts: learning, mastery, discipline, health, and
      exam temperament. Our tools strengthen each part while keeping the whole in view.
    </p>

    <div class="mt-10 grid gap-6 md:grid-cols-2">
      <article class="rounded-2xl border bg-card p-6 shadow-sm">
        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold">Learning</h3>
        <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-muted-foreground">
          Learn actively, not passively. Convert concepts into your own words, solve short problems as you
          read, teach back to a peer or to yourself. Understanding compounds when you engage.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article class="rounded-2xl border bg-card p-6 shadow-sm">
        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold">Mastery</h3>
        <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-muted-foreground">
          Mastery blends two axes: how much you retain and how difficult the material you can handle is.
          We support techniques that raise both.
        </p>
        <ul class="mt-4 list-disc space-y-2 pl-5 text-sm text-muted-foreground">
          <li><span class="font-medium text-foreground">Active recall</span> and <span class="font-medium text-foreground">elaboration</span> to make knowledge retrievable.</li>
          <li><span class="font-medium text-foreground">Spaced repetition</span> to fight forgetting and stabilize memory.</li>
          <li><span class="font-medium text-foreground">Interleaving</span> to build flexible understanding across topics.</li>
          <li>
            The <span class="font-medium text-foreground">Goldilocks zone</span>: practice that is not too easy, not too hard—just
            beyond comfort—so skill grows steadily.
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="font-medium text-foreground">Progressive overload</span>: gradated question sets and mixed reviews that
            expand depth and breadth over time.
          </li>
        </ul>
      </article>

      <article class="rounded-2xl border bg-card p-6 shadow-sm">
        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold">Discipline</h3>
        <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-muted-foreground">
          Consistency beats intensity. Schedules, streaks, and tiny wins keep momentum. We design
          friction-light workflows so showing up is the default.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article class="rounded-2xl border bg-card p-6 shadow-sm">
        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold">Health</h3>
        <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-muted-foreground">
          Learning should fit real life. Some of our tools are designed so students can learn while
          walking in the park—audio prompts, quick recall, and light-touch reviews.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article class="rounded-2xl border bg-card p-6 shadow-sm md:col-span-2">
        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold">Exam Temperament</h3>
        <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-muted-foreground">
          Tests reward calm, clarity, and pacing. We simulate real conditions, provide time-bound drills,
          and help you develop a steady, confident rhythm for exam day.
        </p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section id="competitive-exams" class="container mx-auto px-4 py-10 md:py-14">
    <div class="rounded-2xl border bg-gradient-to-br from-amber-50 to-lime-50 p-8 shadow-sm">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold tracking-tight">Built for competitive exams</h2>
      <p class="mt-2 max-w-3xl text-muted-foreground">
        Competitive preparation demands both speed and depth. Our AI tools craft question sets in the
        Goldilocks zone, schedule spaced reviews automatically, and surface weak spots before they cost
        marks. Students, teachers, and institutes see aligned views of progress.
      </p>
      <div class="mt-6 flex flex-wrap gap-3">
        <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 rounded-full bg-primary px-5 py-2.5 text-primary-foreground text-sm font-medium shadow-sm hover:bg-primary/90">Explore tools</a>
        <a href="/students" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 rounded-full border px-5 py-2.5 text-sm font-medium hover:bg-accent">For students</a>
        <a href="/teachers" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 rounded-full border px-5 py-2.5 text-sm font-medium hover:bg-accent">For teachers</a>
        <a href="/institutes" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 rounded-full border px-5 py-2.5 text-sm font-medium hover:bg-accent">For institutes</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="container mx-auto px-4 py-16">
    <div class="rounded-2xl border p-8 text-center shadow-sm">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold">A simple promise</h2>
      <p class="mx-auto mt-2 max-w-2xl text-muted-foreground">
        If a student is truly at the center, everything else should get simpler: what to study now,
        how to practice next, and how to know you are improving. That is what we build.
      </p>
      <div class="mt-6">
        <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 rounded-full bg-primary px-5 py-3 text-primary-foreground shadow-sm hover:bg-primary/90">Try our AI tools →</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout> 